#: ../../P/plonk.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet: possibly influenced by British slang ‘plonk’ for cheap booze, or "
"‘plonker’ for someone behaving stupidly (latter is lit. equivalent to "
"Yiddish *schmuck*\\)] The sound a :ref:`newbie` makes as he falls to the "
"bottom of a :ref:`kill-file`\\. While it originated in the :ref:`newsgroup` "
":samp:`talk.bizarre`\\, this term (usually written \"\\*plonk\\*\") is now "
"(1994) widespread on Usenet as a form of public ridicule."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet:安酒を表すイギリスのスラング‘plonk’、あるいは愚かな振る舞いをする者を表す‘plonker’(後者は文字通りイディッシュ語の "
"*schmuck* に相当する)の影響を受けた可能性がある]\\ :ref:`newbie`\\ が\\ :ref:`kill-file`\\ "
"の底へ落ちていくときに立てる音。\\ :ref:`newsgroup`\\ の\\ :samp:`talk.bizarre`\\ "
"で生まれたものだが、この用語は(通常\"\\*plonk\\*\\ "
"\"と書かれる)今や(1994年)公の嘲笑の一形態としてUsenet上で広まっている。"
